					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying in survey No. 234 about 1/2 k.m. to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>1665 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Viśvāvasu, Jyēshṭha ba. 7, Thursday. The record may be assigned to the 17th century on the basis of palaeography. During this century the cyclic year Viśvāvasu corresponds to 1604 and 1665 A.D. However, the details of the date of the epiraph regularly correspond to 1665 A.D., May 25, f.d.t. 24.</p>						

						<p>It records the planting the pillars by Pedanēṇḍu, son of Tomṭakūra Mallinēdu Poṭḷūru.</p>						

						</summary>
